cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses information diffusion in networks, including rumor spreading on online social networks, which falls under the scope of cs.SI.
2. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper presents a new source localization algorithm, which can be considered a software engineering problem.
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new algorithm for source localization, which is a problem in data structures and algorithms.
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the spread of malware on the Internet, which falls under the scope of cs.NI.
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper establishes performance guarantees of the proposed algorithm under the independent cascade model, which can be considered an information theory problem.
